the national union for the total independence of angola, which is fighting the communist government with u.s. and south african backing, said it killed 51 angolan soldiers last sunday in tota in the northern coffee-growing province of lunda
the unita rebels said they captured 63 soviet-made ak-47 automatic rifles and destroyed three trucks
in another attack, the group said it shot down the soviet-built mi-28 helicopter, killing its cuban crew, close to the southern town of menongue. the statement did not say how many cubans were on board or give the date of the attack
in the third attack, the rebels said they killed six enemy soldiers from an army patrol monday near the town of luma-kassai in lunda province
the statement gave rebel casualties in the attacks as four killed and seven wounded
there was no independent confirmation of the claims
unita has been fighting since 1975 to force the cuban- and soviet-backed government to share power in the former portuguese colony
if officials in china can work out the details, a chinese-owned winery next year might join the growing lineup of foreign-owned california wineries
so far china has never had a winery outside of china; we have to make research first,'' guo song-quon, chief winemaker of a leading chinese winery, said friday through an interpreter
guo's place of business is tianjin's 80,000-case-a-year heavenly palace winery south of beijing
heavenly palace has been marketing its ``spring moon'' brand in the united states since september, mostly in chinese restaurants. the wine, a medium-dry, fruity muscat, is the only export label in the heavenly palace line
china has been making an intensive effort to earn foreign exchange as fast as possible, and a quality california winery _ participating in a strong premium wine boom _ would help in that direction
at last count, there were 39 foreign-owned wineries out of about 650 in california
if the chinese join the lineup, their foreign colleagues in this state would include british, five wineries; canadians, seven; french, 11; west germans, two; belgians, one; swiss, five; spanish, two; japanese, five; and thais, 1
guo, the son of guo qichang, china's senior winemaker and a top official of the china's ministry of light industry, has been on a whirlwind tour of california wineries this week, he said in an interview
i will make a full report that will go back to the chinese government,'' said guo, who has visited wineries in the sonoma, napa and central valleys. he expressed admiration for the california style of winemaking
especially under study, said guo, is the american system of wine-marketing
what is marketing?'' he said, expressing the question as a statement. ``in china, we don't understand marketing ... even bottling ... we have a lot of problems with bottling in china; there is nothing modern like in california. we want china to follow the american (wine) system.''
