widespread street flooding was reported across the new orleans area and north of lake pontchartrain. rainfall amounts in the new orleans area ranged up to 9 inches since friday evening, with 8.17 inches at gretna and 6.09 inches at gramercy. in east-central louisiana, 5.65 inches fell at bayou sorrel
during the six hours up to 1 p.m. est, 2.08 inches of rain fell at new orleans' lakefront airport
strong thunderstorms developed during the afternoon across parts of eastern iowa and northwestern illinois. showers were scattered from western nebraska through southern minnesota and northern illinois, with most rain amounts less than an inch
