vernon w. thomson, a former wisconsin governor, member of congress for 14 years and federal election commission chairman, died saturday at george washington university hospital, a spokeswoman said. he was 82
yvonne hiott, the hospital spokeswoman, said the cause of death was respiratory arrest. she said thomson, who lived in the washington suburb of mclean, va., had been in the hospital since march 25
thomson, a republican member of the wisconsin state assembly between 1935-51 and speaker for three consecutive terms, served as wisconsin's governor in 1956 and 1957. he was elected to the u.s. house of representatives in november 1960, and served through 1974
after leaving congress, he joined the fec and remained there until 1979, serving in 1976-77 as its chairman
in 1981, then-president jimmy carter called thomson out of retirement to serve a year as interim member of the commission
carter's request that he rejoin the fec illustrated the government's respect for thomson, said former rep. glenn r. davis, r-wis., who described thomson as a friend ever since they served in the wisconsin legislature together in the 1940s
he served longer than he was supposed to,'' davis said saturday. ``i think he was one of the most respected members who ever served in the house.''
born in richland center, wis., thomson attended carroll college and the university of wisconsin law school before serving as richland county district attorney in the 1930s and as richland center mayor
after serving in the state legislature, he was elected state attorney general in 1950, 1952 and 1954 before being named governor for two years. he lost a re-election bid to the statehouse
davis said thomson's re-election defeat in 1958 was the only serious setback in his political career
unfortunately, 1958 was a bad year for republicans,'' davis said
thomson is survived by three children _ vernon jr. of mclean, patricia thomson of fletcher, va., and susan thomson turner of vienna, va. _ and two grandchildren. his wife, the former helen a. davis, died in 1973
funeral services were scheduled for thursday at pratt funeral home in richland center. burial will be at the richland center cemetery
