for sunday's easter egg hunt in terre haute, ind., organizers were plotting how to foil overzealous parents who cheat to help their children win prizes. more than 1,000 children were expected to participate in the event at deming park in one of indiana's biggest annual easter egg hunts
in the past adults have painted winning numbers on eggs, or found the highly coveted gold and silver eggs and passed them off to their kids, said georgeo schoffstall of the american legion, which sponsors the event
sixty monitors will be on hand to keep parents from collecting any of the nearly 2,000 hidden eggs. ``we could use a 150,'' schoffstall said
for more than 50 years, passers-by in bement, ill., marveled at the thousands of colored eggs, plastic rabbits and ducks, and statues of geese and goslings that adorned zenaida drake's yard
although mrs. drake died last fall at age 73, her spirit lives on, thanks to some old-fashioned community spirit and mrs. drake's husband, bill, who donated the decorations to the bement community council
some of the council members went to the drake home on friday, and the bement girl scout troop pitched in to set out the same decorations that the russian woman had displayed for nearly half a century, many of which she had made herself
she always told us that in the old country, they decorated for easter like we do for christmas, so she brought the tradition with her,'' said gary jennings, president of the council
